1
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:23,200
Who is this?  You caught me by surprise.

2
00:00:24,050 --> 00:00:26,510
Hello, Professor.

3
00:00:26,510 --> 00:00:31,130
Nam Ju Wan and Professor Kang are somehow connected.

4
00:00:31,130 --> 00:00:32,970
We should be careful.

5
00:00:32,970 --> 00:00:35,090
- Do you live nearby?
- No.

6
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:38,930
So how did you know about this place?

7
00:00:41,690 --> 00:00:44,420
I come by sometimes to listen to the music.

8
00:00:46,470 --> 00:00:48,700
Have a seat.  Would you like something to drink?

9
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:51,950
No.  I was just on my way out for an appointment.

10
00:00:51,950 --> 00:00:56,240
Sir.  I'll come by next time again.

11
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:59,510
What?  Are you leaving already?

12
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:05,100
I got an urgent  call from home.   I'll come listen to music next time.

13
00:01:05,160 --> 00:01:07,070
Yes.

14
00:01:07,850 --> 00:01:11,540
I'm sorry.  I'm going.

15
00:01:21,620 --> 00:01:25,800
Auxerre Cathedral: 800th anniversary
James Kauffman on the  Great Organ of the cathedral

16
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:29,100
How did you kill Yun Yeong Gil?

17
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:31,900
Did you push him here?

18
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,130
You killed someone and then went to conduct a performance.

19
00:01:52,130 --> 00:01:56,200
Did you enjoy holding the baton in the hand which just killed someone?

20
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:59,780
Do you still want to be respected after doing that?

21
00:02:02,140 --> 00:02:07,180
What about you?  You're the suspect, not me.

22
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:11,570
Finally, you're reaching the bottom.

23
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:15,990
I'm sorry, but it's a long way to get to the bottom.

24
00:02:18,890 --> 00:02:21,800
I will find it. Whatever you hid.

25
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:26,530
I'm going to personally watch you fall to the bottom.

26
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:30,190
Please do so.

27
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:47,410
I Wanna Hear Your Song

28
00:02:49,790 --> 00:02:54,460
It's been a long time since I had a drink with my student. Why are you running away?

29
00:02:54,460 --> 00:02:56,640
I'm not running away.  I have an appointment.

30
00:02:56,700 --> 00:03:01,400
Which way are you going?  I have a lot of time today and will give you a ride.

31
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:07,400
Didn't you come here to listen to music? I'm fine.

32
00:03:14,420 --> 00:03:16,780
I said I'll take you there.

33
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:35,000
Recently things have been messy, haven't they? A murder, and suspects everywhere.

34
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:39,350
The twentieth anniversary is soon.  The foundation's image has been tarnished too.

35
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,390
I also feel like my blood is drying up.

36
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:45,980
I heard you're assisting Conductor Nam. Do you enjoy that job?

37
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,630
Yes.

38
00:03:49,610 --> 00:03:52,750
That café, earlier ... do you go there often?

39
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:59,120
Well, sometimes. You're a young person.  Why do you go there?

40
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:04,700
Did you know Yun Yeong Gil?

41
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:08,310
The person who died at the Sinyeong Philharmonic Building not long ago.

42
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:14,770
Actually, that café was his favorite.

43
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:18,950
Is that so? I didn't know.

44
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:21,100
How did you know?

45
00:04:22,150 --> 00:04:26,240
He worked part-time at my family's shop.  That's when I heard that.

46
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:29,190
At your family's shop?

47
00:04:29,190 --> 00:04:30,810
Yes.

48
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:37,810
Professor, why did you go the café earlier?

49
00:04:37,810 --> 00:04:42,450
No matter how hard I think about it, I don't think it's the kind of place you would frequent.

50
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:47,750
Could it be that you knew Yun Yeong Gil?

51
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:54,490
What kind of question are you asking?  How would I know someone like that?

52
00:04:54,490 --> 00:04:59,310
- Did you hear something somewhere?
- No. Nothing like that.

53
00:04:59,310 --> 00:05:02,400
So why ask me such a strange question?

54
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,760
I'm sorry.

55
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,880
Why exactly do you say things for which you'll be sorry?

56
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:15,590
It's a case of murder.  You shouldn't imply someone is involved.

57
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,300
It's offensive.

58
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:38,500
Is your house near here?  My goodness, you live high.

59
00:05:39,530 --> 00:05:43,270
Thank you for bringing me here. I'll go on in.

60
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:50,900
- You, ... did you often meet Yun Yeong Gil, the man who died?
- What?

61
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:56,900
You said he worked part-time for your family. Did he say something to you before he died?

62
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:03,910
No, he didn't say anything. We weren't that close.

63
00:06:03,910 --> 00:06:08,970
Do the police know you knew him?

64
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,060
I can't say.

65
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:14,600
I have no idea.

66
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:18,490
Watching you earlier, you should keep your mouth shut.

67
00:06:18,490 --> 00:06:22,000
I mean, you blurt things out indiscriminately.

68
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,080
Why are you going to the café frequented by the dead person?

69
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:28,100
What would you have to gain by doing that?

70
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:31,990
If you aren't careful, you could really be implicated in a murder case.

71
00:06:31,990 --> 00:06:36,020
You still have your future before you.  Is that how you are going to use it?

72
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:47,000
Don't be afraid.  I'm just saying to take care of yourself.

73
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:51,250
What are you doing?

74
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:56,150
Why do I see him here, of all places?

75
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:01,290
Go home. Hurry.

76
00:07:01,290 --> 00:07:03,980
Lock the door.

77
00:07:03,980 --> 00:07:09,400
Hey. Is it all right for a murder suspect to walk around freely, like this?

78
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:12,740
Since when did Korean law become this way?

79
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:16,580
I'm sorry, but the court released me.

80
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:19,000
Why did you bring Hong Yi Yeong here?

81
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:24,610
What, a teacher can't give a student a ride? I brought her home.

82
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:29,320
It's kidnapping to put her in a car without her consent.  Did you know that?

83
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:33,510
Also, you pressured the police, didn't you?

84
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:37,620
You told them to lock me up. Why did you do that?

85
00:07:38,290 --> 00:07:39,370
What the hell are you talking about?

86
00:07:39,370 --> 00:07:43,400
I saw Nam Ju Won taking the bag kept in Yun Yeong Gil's storage locker.

87
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:49,520
And after that I was arrested. Is it possible your weakness is kept in that bag?

88
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:52,300
Did you order Nam Ju Wan to do it?

89
00:07:53,470 --> 00:07:56,830
Jeez.  What kind of novel are you writing by yourself?

90
00:07:56,900 --> 00:08:00,500
I'm warning you, do not to go around threatening people.

91
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:06,960
Wait quietly at home. I'm going to put you where I am right now, as soon as possible. Understand?

92
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:13,200
It's a crime to threaten someone without any evidence.  Do you know that?

93
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:19,500
I know. After being held in a detention center for murder, what is there to fear in threatening someone?

94
00:08:23,490 --> 00:08:25,530
Bastard.

95
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:37,100
My younger brother died a year ago. He was stabbed with a knife then run over by a car.

96
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:40,790
Nam Ju Wan just said you did it.

97
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:45,430
If your prized pupil says such a thing to you, there must be some reason, don't you agree?

98
00:08:46,350 --> 00:08:51,020
I recorded everything you two said.

99
00:08:52,290 --> 00:08:55,850
I'll take my time considering when and how to use this.

100
00:08:55,850 --> 00:09:00,340
Is it possible your weakness is kept in that bag?

101
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:02,430
Did you order Nam Ju Wan to do it?

102
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:28,500
Yun Yeong Gil wanted me to tell you this. He said people are not the only ones who can see.

103
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:03,180
You look fine for someone who's been through the wringer.

104
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:07,060
When did you get out?

105
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:08,810
Today.

106
00:10:08,810 --> 00:10:11,480
Have you been cleared of all charges?

107
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:15,030
First of all, there's no evidence.

108
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:18,090
Is your album preparation going well?

109
00:10:18,090 --> 00:10:21,430
Don't pretend to care. You're not interested in that.

110
00:10:22,460 --> 00:10:24,770
Why did you want to see me?

111
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:34,370
On the day Yun Yeong Gil died, I saw Nam Ju Wan go to his storage locker.

112
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:38,390
Nam Ju Wan took Yun Yeong Gil's bag from there.

113
00:10:39,590 --> 00:10:42,470
What are you talking about?

114
00:10:42,470 --> 00:10:48,790
Do you perhaps suspect that the conductor killed him?

115
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:53,290
Why would he do such a thing?

116
00:10:54,110 --> 00:10:56,980
You know that Yun Yeong Gil was the driver in my brother's hit-and-run accident, right?

117
00:10:56,980 --> 00:11:01,610
He was the only one who knew the complete facts of that day.  Except for Hong Yi Yeong.

118
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,970
You mean she is a witness?

119
00:11:03,970 --> 00:11:08,690
Yes, she's a witness. She finally regained her memory.

120
00:11:08,690 --> 00:11:16,600
She said the conductor came with a knife in the warehouse where she was with my brother.

121
00:11:17,590 --> 00:11:20,160
With a knife?

122
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:24,350
At this point, this is just my guess.

123
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:30,880
I think the bag which Nam Ju Wan took held the object which caused my brother's death.

124
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:34,620
The object you mention, what is it?

125
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:39,160
It's the ballpoint pen which Sinyeong Music College made to give to the faculty members.

126
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:41,600
I called you because I'd like your help in finding it.

127
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:45,380
Me? Why are you asking me?

128
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:48,150
You're involved in this. Didn't you get involved because of Nam Ju Wan?

129
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:52,400
Don't shift responsibility to me. The conductor might not be the culprit.

130
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:57,300
Without any evidence, this is only your belief. So how can I trust you?

131
00:11:57,300 --> 00:12:01,540
I have a video of Nam Ju Wan taking the bag.

132
00:12:03,650 --> 00:12:05,790
It's not proof that he killed someone.

133
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:08,290
It is proof that he was involved with the dead man.

134
00:12:08,290 --> 00:12:14,170
Professor Kang, Yun Yeong Gil and Nam Joo Wan, these three are definitely connected to each other.

135
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:20,500
Are you going to just let Nam Joo Wan get away with it?  Do you still like him?

136
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:31,050
Come in.

137
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:44,670
Have you been drinking a lot?

138
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:50,730
A bit. You said you wanted to see me hit the bottom. Isn't that why you came here?

139
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:55,350
I just met with Jang Yun.

140
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:57,130
So?

141
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:02,310
He said that on the day Kim Ian had his accident, a year ago,

142
00:13:02,310 --> 00:13:05,770
you were on the scene.

143
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:11,070
And he said that the murder or Yun Yeong Gil is also your doing.

144
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:14,940
So, have you come here because you believed what he said?

145
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:17,900
Because you also want to make me into a murderer?

146
00:13:18,660 --> 00:13:22,120
It's only that your being involved with Professor Kang troubles me.

147
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:28,580
I know very well that when you were a student, you studied thanks to his support.

148
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:32,330
Have you done his dirty work for him since then?

149
00:13:32,330 --> 00:13:38,140
Is it true that he supported your becoming the conductor of the Sinyeong Philharmonic?

150
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:42,070
Did he possibly make you get involved in that accident last year?

151
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:45,900
- That's not so.
- Then, what is it?

152
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:52,090
I know you won't tell me the truth, but actually I'm very worried.

153
00:13:52,090 --> 00:13:56,700
I told you not to be concerned about me and to work on your own career.

154
00:13:56,700 --> 00:14:02,630
How nice it would  be  to do just as you say.

155
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:11,470
You didn't kill that man Yun Yeong Gil, did you?

156
00:14:13,650 --> 00:14:16,310
Why are you doing this to me, too?

157
00:14:16,310 --> 00:14:19,120
I don't want to believe it either.

158
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:25,590
But if you really killed someone,

159
00:14:25,590 --> 00:14:29,260
I would like you to turn yourself in.

160
00:14:31,930 --> 00:14:36,750
That way I think I won't feel that

161
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:39,640
the time I spent loving you was wasted.

162
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,490
Come in.

163
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:59,400
- You haven't had dinner yet, right?
- Yeah.

164
00:15:01,290 --> 00:15:03,890
- Did you go to the market?
- Yes.

165
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:06,530
What is this? When you must have been shocked from meeting Professor Kang?

166
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:09,400
If you were hungry, you should have just called me to go out to eat.

167
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:15,200
I didn't want to eat out on a day like today. And I wasn't that shocked.

168
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:19,830
What did I buy? Guess.

169
00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:22,010
What is that?

170
00:15:22,010 --> 00:15:24,150
Tofu.
(Symbol of purity, traditionally eaten by someone released from prison)

171
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:27,630
Are you saying I have to eat that?

172
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:29,580
Anyway, you were released from the detention center.

173
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:31,900
I don' t want to eat that.

174
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:36,300
You can't refuse.  It signifies that you aren't going back again.

175
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:41,350
There, relax.  I'll make you some tofu kimchi.

176
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,400
- You'll make it?
- Yes.

177
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:55,200
- Never mind.  I'll do it.
- No, I'll do it.

178
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:59,070
You're tired. Go and  rest.  I'll do it.

179
00:15:59,070 --> 00:16:01,400
I'll do it.

180
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:25,060
Do you want me to feed you this?

181
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:27,580
Never mind.

182
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:29,650
I don't want you to.  It's fine.

183
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:40,480
Yummy.

184
00:16:45,130 --> 00:16:47,300
Where did you run into Professor Kang?

185
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:49,200
At an LP cafe.

186
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:54,400
Because it was strange, I asked him why he came  and if he knew Yun Yeong Gil.

187
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:57,710
It seems you weren't afraid to ask that.

188
00:16:58,380 --> 00:17:01,020
I think what you say is correct.

189
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:05,510
Professor Kang definitely is connected to the case.

190
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:08,250
What did the café owner say?

191
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:12,440
He said Yun Yeong Gil had left me a gift at the café.

192
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:17,440
I don't know what it is. Professor Kang came  so I just left.

193
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:23,700
Yun Yeong Gil may have died because he knew who killed Ian.

194
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:30,320
Just what could Yun Yeong Gil have left you?

195
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:33,730
It might not be anything significant.  I'll go back.

196
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:37,600
- Call me when you go.  Let's go together.
- I will.

197
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:47,100
- When I think about it, isn't it amazing?
- What is?

198
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:49,430
The class I took with Eun Ju.

199
00:17:49,430 --> 00:17:54,550
You were the teaching assistant so how many times did we meet a few years ago?

200
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:57,430
Without being aware of each other?

201
00:17:57,430 --> 00:17:59,160
Indeed.

202
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,960
Do you remember me?

203
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:08,000
- Yeah.
- Really?

204
00:18:09,380 --> 00:18:11,150
No.

205
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:17,740
I don't remember you either. Anyway, it's amazing.

206
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:21,470
I think you meet the person you're supposed to meet somehow or other.

207
00:18:22,710 --> 00:18:28,030
Are you a little upset that I don't call you by your real name?

208
00:18:28,030 --> 00:18:32,590
No, I understand.  It's hard to do that suddenly.

209
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:36,380
I will gradually  get used to it and call you by that name.

210
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:44,670
Jang Do Hun.

211
00:18:56,100 --> 00:19:01,960
Yes, it's me.  You went out suddenly at dinner time and didn't call.    Aren't you coming back today?

212
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:07,920
Today, I will sleep at my place. Actually, Yun was released today.

213
00:19:09,030 --> 00:19:13,910
I understand. Mom was disturbed when you left and told me about it.

214
00:19:13,910 --> 00:19:15,370
Aunt did?

215
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:20,200
She must have seen him before when he escorted you home.  Have all the charges been dropped?

216
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:22,650
He was released because there's no evidence.

217
00:19:22,650 --> 00:19:27,200
I told you that he would never do such a thing.

218
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:30,800
That's all good.  But you shouldn't be involved with Jang Yun.

219
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:33,030
You are also entangled in this case.

220
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:36,420
If something goes wrong, everything from a year ago could be brought up.

221
00:19:36,420 --> 00:19:38,160
Are you listening to what I'm saying?

222
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:42,330
I am sorry, but I can't do that.

223
00:19:42,330 --> 00:19:46,860
No matter what you say, I'm going to do whatever I can.

224
00:19:47,810 --> 00:19:49,640
Bye.

225
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:17,650
Let's pass the audition!    Rule the world of Timpani.

226
00:20:17,650 --> 00:20:19,920
The Best Works of Mozart.

227
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,760
I can do it.  You can do it.

228
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,900
Audition

229
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:41,740
Jang Do Hun ❤︎ 😊❤︎

230
00:21:01,950 --> 00:21:04,150
So are you saying I killed two people?

231
00:21:04,150 --> 00:21:07,400
Am I some murdering fiend who goes around killing people?

232
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:10,420
How dare you say such things?

233
00:21:10,420 --> 00:21:13,360
Professor, please stop making excuses.

234
00:21:14,890 --> 00:21:18,350
Copying

235
00:21:51,250 --> 00:21:55,600
We've met once before, haven't we? At our shop.

236
00:21:55,600 --> 00:22:01,000
Yes.  I went there to buy flowers for the one-year memorial of my brother's death.

237
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,260
Umm.

238
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:06,610
Actually ...

239
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:11,400
even though I don't have any right, I'm  asking a favor.

240
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:18,190
I would like you not to be close to our Yi Yeong.

241
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:24,200
I keep asking her but she won't listen to me. So I am asking you directly.

242
00:22:25,290 --> 00:22:30,800
I don't care if you call me selfish or criticize me, but in this world no parent

243
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:36,900
would let her child see someone who was on the news as a murder suspect.

244
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:45,430
Well. I don't know if you are guilty of the crime.

245
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:50,800
All that I want for Yi Yeong is, someone ordinary,

246
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:54,170
someone who doesn't have a lot of baggage,

247
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:59,200
just someone who cherishes her.

248
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:06,610
Honestly, if she is with you,

249
00:23:06,610 --> 00:23:11,970
can she ever forget last year's incident even for a short while?

250
00:23:11,970 --> 00:23:15,410
It's going to be the same for you.

251
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,190
Ludwig van Beethoven Variations No. 9

252
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:37,940
Are you thinking now of not speaking to me?

253
00:23:37,940 --> 00:23:41,220
I'm not sure of what to say.

254
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,280
Did you call me?

255
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:54,460
Come in.  You've worked hard.

256
00:23:54,460 --> 00:23:58,090
Starting today, I don't want you to come to the rehearsals.

257
00:23:58,090 --> 00:24:02,390
Although it is unfair,  the orchestra members' attitude is my first priority.

258
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:05,290
I understand and will do so.

259
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:08,470
The 20th anniversary concert is postponed for now.

260
00:24:08,470 --> 00:24:10,700
This doesn't mean that I should leave, does it?

261
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:14,970
Don't magnify the significance. It's literally postponed.

262
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:20,000
I want you to continue your personal practice.  You may leave.

263
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:36,580
You didn't have to take him out of the rehearsals.

264
00:24:36,580 --> 00:24:41,070
Since when did I allow an assistant to question what I say?

265
00:24:42,540 --> 00:24:43,650
I'm sorry.

266
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:46,660
Are you intending to continue working in this atmosphere?

267
00:24:46,660 --> 00:24:49,210
Yes.

268
00:24:49,210 --> 00:24:51,350
Why?

269
00:24:52,300 --> 00:24:56,370
I will stick to you until you tell me everything

270
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:59,100
you've done with your own mouth.

271
00:25:00,060 --> 00:25:02,550
Then we are going to be together a long time.

272
00:25:06,010 --> 00:25:08,800
- I think we can proceed like that.
- Yes.

273
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,660
Yes?

274
00:25:13,450 --> 00:25:17,290
Welcome.  You've had an ordeal.

275
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:22,000
Assistant Yang, would you like to get some coffee?

276
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,800
Oh, yes.

277
00:25:29,170 --> 00:25:31,000
Have a seat.

278
00:25:36,830 --> 00:25:40,950
I would like to hear what exactly is happening now.

279
00:25:40,950 --> 00:25:45,770
I've been released because there is no evidence. I will continue to be investigated.

280
00:25:46,630 --> 00:25:49,830
Are you certain you had nothing to do with the person who died in our building?

281
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:52,060
I didn't do it.

282
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:57,710
I believe you too, but I'm getting pressured here and there.

283
00:25:57,710 --> 00:26:00,560
Why did you ask to see me today?

284
00:26:01,190 --> 00:26:06,520
You're in charge of managing all of the Sinyeong Philharmonic  aren't you?

285
00:26:07,180 --> 00:26:09,500
I didn't know you were interested in my work.

286
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:13,380
I've always been very interested in the Sinyeong Philharmonic.

287
00:26:13,380 --> 00:26:15,590
From a request to my father's secretary,

288
00:26:15,590 --> 00:26:20,450
I obtained and reviewed ten years of the Philharmonic's accounting records.

289
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:25,550
The secretary is so competent.

290
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:27,930
Facility Leases

291
00:26:27,930 --> 00:26:31,300
He even found things which were covered up.

292
00:26:31,300 --> 00:26:34,280
Wait a minute. Just what are you alleging... ?

293
00:26:34,300 --> 00:26:37,520
I know everything you've done here.

294
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:40,480
Starting with taking the facility rents from  the corporate funds,

295
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:43,400
inflated expenses through false expenditure resolutions,

296
00:26:43,420 --> 00:26:45,240
--what was it -- performance hall rental fees,

297
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:48,630
purchase of musical instruments, service fees,  all pocketed.

298
00:26:48,630 --> 00:26:52,830
And It's not in the records, but the details of the chairwoman's use of the corporate credit card are spectacular.

299
00:26:52,900 --> 00:26:55,550
Stop it.

300
00:26:55,550 --> 00:26:59,000
In order to keep the Sinyeong Philharmonic running, it couldn't be helped. That was my job.

301
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:05,150
I'm sure it was. But how many years will you serve if this is given to the prosecutor?

302
00:27:05,150 --> 00:27:08,150
Are you okay with being the scapegoat?

303
00:27:10,890 --> 00:27:16,300
Jang Yun. Why are you doing this to me?

304
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:18,830
What do you want?

305
00:27:18,830 --> 00:27:22,980
Chairman Jang asked me to tell you this.

306
00:27:23,990 --> 00:27:27,630
If you want us to bury this, you must bring us something bigger.

307
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:32,960
Bring it together with a reason to fire Conductor Nam Ju Wan.

308
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:55,290
Is the conductor not in?

309
00:27:55,290 --> 00:27:57,960
Yes.  He's not here.

310
00:27:58,890 --> 00:28:03,860
Excuse me. I have a question, Assistant Yang.

311
00:28:03,860 --> 00:28:05,080
A question for me?

312
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:10,880
Right before the concert, the conductor disappeared and  you were desperately searching for him.

313
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:12,210
Yes.

314
00:28:12,210 --> 00:28:17,140
How many people knew he had disappeared and were looking for him?

315
00:28:17,140 --> 00:28:21,970
Three people.  Manager Yun, Hong Yi Yeong and I.

316
00:28:21,970 --> 00:28:24,100
I see.

317
00:28:25,540 --> 00:28:28,210
Do you know the stairs where Yun Yeong Gil died?

318
00:28:28,210 --> 00:28:33,360
Were you ever near the exit to that stairway that day?

319
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:35,630
No, I ...

320
00:28:38,620 --> 00:28:41,510
I didn't go in that direction.

321
00:28:41,510 --> 00:28:44,700
- Is that so?
- Yes.

322
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:48,600
Alright.  You may go.

323
00:28:57,800 --> 00:29:00,380
The rooftop.
